What you need to know:

The plan says the lobby would push for mainstreaming of agriculture policies and laws, financing and for a competitive and enabling business environment.Asnet chairman Bimal Kantaria said the launch of the document would help the sector overcome the adverse effects of the Covid-19 pandemic that have affected productivity in the industry.Fisheries PS Micheni Ntiba, who attended the event, called for more participation in deep-sea and ocean fisheries, restating that the government pledged its support for the sub-sector.Livestock PS Harry Kimutai noted that an uncoordinated, fragmented agriculture private sector creates the perfect conditions for brokers and other unscrupulous dealings to thrive.Â 